            <section id="qr-method" class="guide-section">
                <h2>Method 1: QR Code Transfer (3DS/Wii U/Tomodachi Life/Miitomo)</h2>
                
                <div class="method-overview">
                    <strong>Best for:</strong> 3DS ‚Üî Wii U, 3DS ‚Üî Tomodachi Life, Any system ‚Üí 3DS/Wii U
                    <strong>Difficulty:</strong> Easy
                </div>
                
                <h3>Exporting a Mii to QR Code:</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Open <strong>Mii Maker</strong> on your 3DS or Wii U</li>
                    <li>Select the Mii you want to export</li>
                    <li>Tap <strong>"QR Code/Image Options"</strong></li>
                    <li>Choose <strong>"Save Mii as QR Code"</strong></li>
                    <li>The QR code will be saved to your SD card in the <code>DCIM</code> folder</li>
                </ol>
                
                <h3>Importing a Mii from QR Code:</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Display the QR code on another device (phone, computer, or print it)</li>
                    <li>Open <strong>Mii Maker</strong> on your 3DS or Wii U</li>
                    <li>Tap <strong>"QR Code/Image Options"</strong></li>
                    <li>Choose <strong>"Scan QR Code"</strong></li>
                    <li>Point your camera at the QR code</li>
                    <li>Tap <strong>"OK"</strong> to save the Mii</li>
                </ol>
                
                <div class="pro-tip">
                    <strong>üí° Pro Tip:</strong> Use InfiniMii to generate QR codes for any Mii, even those from the Wii or Switch!
