            </section>
            
            <section id="amiibo-method" class="guide-section">
                <h2>Method 2: Amiibo Transfer</h2>
                
                <div class="method-overview">
                    <strong>Best for:</strong> 3DS ‚Üí Switch, Wii U ‚Üí Switch
                    <strong>Requirements:</strong> Amiibo figure, New 3DS/3DS with NFC Reader, or Wii U
                    <strong>Difficulty:</strong> Moderate
                </div>
                
                <h3>Registering a Mii to an Amiibo:</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>On your <strong>3DS</strong> or <strong>Wii U</strong>, go to <strong>System Settings</strong></li>
                    <li>Navigate to <strong>Amiibo Settings</strong></li>
                    <li>Select <strong>"Register Owner and Nickname"</strong></li>
                    <li>Place your Amiibo on the NFC reader</li>
                    <li>Select the Mii you want to register</li>
                    <li>Complete the registration process</li>
                </ol>
                
                <h3>Using the Amiibo Mii on Switch:</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>On your <strong>Nintendo Switch</strong>, go to <strong>System Settings</strong></li>
                    <li>Select <strong>Mii</strong> ‚Üí <strong>Create/Edit a Mii</strong></li>
                    <li>Choose <strong>"Add New Mii"</strong> ‚Üí <strong>"Copy Mii from amiibo"</strong></li>
                    <li>Place the Amiibo on the right Joy-Con stick or Pro Controller NFC point</li>
                    <li>The Mii will be copied to your Switch</li>
                </ol>
                
                <div class="warning-box">
                    <strong>‚ö†Ô∏è Note:</strong> Each Amiibo can only have ONE registered owner Mii at a time. Registering a new Mii will overwrite the previous one.
                </div>
            </section>
            
            <section id="wii-remote" class="guide-section">
                <h2>Method 3: Wii Remote Connection</h2>
                
